The paper deals with error-correcting codes in the rank metric, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves algebraic structures such as root spaces and idempotent generators, which are relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). The study of lattices and bounds on minimum distance is related to optimization and algorithms (cs.SI), while the analysis of linear codes over a base field is a topic in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
